    "questionText": "You are checking a site report for a new sub-main installation. The report notes the 'physical length' of the cable is 45 and the 'potential difference' (voltage) at the consumer unit is 400. State the correct SI unit names and symbols for both of these measurements to ensure the technical record is accurate.",
